headlines.description: Wolves shared the spoils for the sixth time in 10 Premier League games as Jonny equalised in the second half to earn them a 1-1 draw at Newcastle.
Arsenal threw a two-goal lead to draw 2-2 against Crystal Palace at the Emirates on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arsenal let 2-goal lead slip; Xhaka storms off

headlines.description: Liverpool came from behind to beat Tottenham 2-1 at Anfield and go six points clear at the top of the Premier League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henderson, Salah send Liverpool six clear

headlines.description: Manchester United missed two penalties but still managed to secure their first league road win for eight months in a 3-1 victory at Norwich.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utd survive two missed penalties in Norwich win
